Police say the 34-year-old was a taxi driver from Bellville. CAPE TOWN - A man has been shot dead at the Huguenot Train Station in Paarl. Police said that the 34-year-old was a taxi driver from Bellville. He was gunned down during the early hours of Tuesday morning. The police's Frederick van Wyk said: “Any possibility that the incident is linked to a murder in Paarl East last night is not ruled out, Any person with any information regarding this shooting incident is kindly requested to call Crime Stop on 08600 10111.”